Walkthrough: TightBinding.jl
What was accomplished
I've implemented a new Julia package, TightBinding.jl, leveraging WannierIO to read Wannier90 hopping integrals and build a tight-binding model. The package evaluates the Hamiltonian $H(\mathbf{k})$ accurately in k-space.

Per your request, the project has been fully initialized in the new folder: /home/attacc/SOFTWARE/lumen/TightBinding.

Architecture Details
The package is composed of:

src/model.jl: Defines the TBModel struct and the read_tb_model function to parse the hr.dat hopping matrices using WannierIO.
src/hamiltonian.jl: Defines hamiltonian(model, k) to construct the exact $H(\mathbf{k})$ hermitian matrix via a sum over the $\mathbf{R}$ vectors.
src/bands.jl: Implements get_bands to iterate through k-points and diagonalize $H(\mathbf{k})$ to obtain energy eigenvalues.
test/runtests.jl: We've included an automated test that validates the correct matrix evaluations and band structure parsing with a mock 1D chain data file.
Validation Results
All automated tests passed successfully, covering reading, parsing, pointwise evaluation, and band extraction.

To build on this package, you can now cd to /home/attacc/SOFTWARE/lumen/TightBinding and run julia --project=@. -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.test()' at your convenience.
